t's%20%26quot%3Bfractional%20boardroom%26quot%3B%20is%20driven%20by%20leaders%20who%20want%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20model%20offers%20flexibility%20and%20access%20to%20executive-level%20talent%20for%20startups.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHolding%20out%20for%20the%20gold%20Rolex%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhen-can-i-retire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhen%20you%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20the%20goal%20for%20many%20leaders%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Gannett%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Gannett.Partners%2C%20believes%20fractional%20leadership%20is%20the%20way%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20launched%20a%20new%20leadership%20model%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bfractional%20boardroom%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20changing%20nature%20of%20work.%20More%20professionals%20are%20seeking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-portfolio-career-pros-cons-income-streams-side-hustles-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eportfolio%20careers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20better%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftime-to-rethink-what-work-life-balance-really-means-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20three%20decades%2C%20Gannett%20has%20built%20a%20%26quot%3Bfabulous%20network%26quot%3B%20of%20talented%20people%20through%20multiple%20career%20reinventions.%20His%20varied%20path%20led%20him%20through%20the%20world%20of%20consumer%20goods%2C%20finance%2C%20and%20media%2C%20from%20Dr.%20Pepper%2C%20Mondelez%2C%20Citibank%2C%20and%20Sony%20Music%20Entertainment%2C%20to%20becoming%20the%20CMO%20of%20American%20Idol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20these%20are%20steps%20that%20cumulatively%20allow%20me%20to%20do%20what%20I%20do%20today%2C%20which%20is%20reinvention%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGannett%2C%2052%2C%20wanted%20to%20invite%20some%20of%20those%20he%20met%20along%20the%20way%20to%20his%20new%20venture%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20help%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-to-grow-a-small-business%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebudding%20entrepreneurs%3C%2Fa%3E%20turn%20their%20visions%20into%20reality%20through%20training%2C%20coaching%2C%20and%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20away%20from%20his%20family%20over%20the%20years%20and%20wanted%20to%20change%20that%20when%20he%20started%20Gannett.Partners%2C%20creating%20a%20fractional%20boardroom%20of%20executives%20who%20felt%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExecutives%20who%20have%20a%20similar%20profile%20to%20myself%2C%20we've%20been%20operating%20for%2020%20and%2030%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Gannett%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20very%20well%20established%20in%20our%20careers.%20We%20want%20more%20agency%2C%20and%20we%20want%20to%20work%20on%20projects%20that%20inspire%20us%2C%20and%20we%20want%20to%20work%20with%20people%20who%20give%20us%20energy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20two%20years%20since%20launching%2C%20Gannett.Partners%20has%20gained%20clients%20in%2010%20countries%20across%2015%20industries%20and%20continues%20to%20expand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279db55b2-fc78-4688-b3b4-5d9adf6caa00%5C%22%3E'Outcomes%2C%20not%20optics'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20members%20of%20the%20fractional%20team%20at%20Gannett.Partners%20are%20Gregg%20Bernard%2C%20the%20CBO%20at%20the%20AI%20video%20platform%20Channel%201%20and%20former%20executive%20of%20WWE%2C%20and%20Rob%20Sender%2C%20who%20was%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20brand%20and%20marketing%20for%20the%20Dallas%20Cowboys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBernard%20told%20BI%20he%20was%20attracted%20to%20the%20fractional%20model%20by%20its%20focus%20on%20%26quot%3Boutcomes%2C%20not%20optics%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20how%20leaders%20can%20bring%20in%20the%20exact%20expertise%20needed%20to%20a%20company%2C%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bsettling%20for%20generalists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20hiring%20someone%20to%20warm%20a%20seat%20or%20deliver%20a%20deck%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20engaging%20a%20group%20of%20seasoned%20operators%20to%20solve%20real%20problems%20at%20high-leverage%20moments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20early-stage%20and%20growth%20companies%2C%20it's%20also%20a%20way%20to%20access%20executive-level%20talent%20that%20would%20otherwise%20be%20out%20of%20reach%2C%20financially%20or%20structurally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBernard%20said%20fractional%20leadership%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmarter%2C%20more%20flexible%20way%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20founders%20%26quot%3Bwill%20feel%20that%20difference%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESender%20told%20BI%20the%20effectiveness%20comes%20from%20diverse%20perspectives%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20the%20commitment%20or%20risk%20of%20hiring%20full-time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEspecially%20in%20the%20early%20stages%2C%20most%20companies%20don't%20need%20%E2%80%94%20or%20can't%20afford%20%E2%80%94%20a%20full-time%20CMO%20or%20COO%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20approach%20gives%20them%20the%20ability%20to%20bring%20in%20experienced%20leaders%20who've%20operated%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%2C%20but%20with%20more%20elasticity%20and%20a%20sharper%20focus%20than%20they'd%20get%20from%20a%20traditional%20consultancy%20or%20playbook-driven%20firm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESender%20said%20that%20for%20him%2C%20he%20gets%20to%20choose%20projects%20that%20genuinely%20excite%20him%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20a%20better%20fit%20when%20he's%20working%20with%20a%20new%20startup.%20If%20there's%20another%20leader%20who%20is%20a%20better%20fit%2C%20that's%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20optionality%20creates%20real%20alignment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20assigning%20work%2C%20you're%20matching%20energy%20and%20expertise%20to%20opportunity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gannett%2C%20culture%20has%20always%20been%20super%20important.%20He%20believes%20that%20with%20a%20fractional%20boardroom%2C%20everyone%20is%20fully%20engaged%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Blearning%20from%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d30e8f9-0cf3-449d-938f-fea19a37f94c%5C%22%3E'Sustainable%20model'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20type%20of%20executive%20that%20we're%20increasingly%20bringing%20around%20us%20is%20these%20folks%20who%20are%20very%20good%20at%20what%20they%20do%2C%20and%20they%20have%20the%20same%20type%20of%20curiosity%20that%20I%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%20working%20on%20projects%20that%20are%20outside%20the%20scope%20of%20their%20day%20job%2C%20which%20they're%20fully%20engaged%20in%20and%20highly%20competent%20at%20doing%2C%20they're%20just%20constantly%20fed%2C%20their%20brain%20is%20fed%2C%20and%20our%20clients%20are%20the%20beneficiaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGannett%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bquite%20bullish%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20future%20of%20fractional%20leadership%2C%20seeing%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20sustainable%20model%20across%20all%20industries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20trying%20to%20operate%20in%20a%20more%20capital-efficient%20way.%20Anyone%20who's%20not%20isn't%20going%20to%20be%20competitive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffractional-leadership-model-disruptive-success-startups-executives-chris-gannett-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749891541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682daebbc6ad288d14818023%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffractional-leadership-model-disruptive-success-startups-executives-chris-gannett-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chris%20Gannett's%20%26quot%3Bfractional%20boardroom%26quot%3B%20leadership%20model%20helps%20seasoned%20executives%20build%20portfolio%20careers%20and%20strike%20a%20better%20work-life%20balance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ldodgson%40businessinsider.com%20(Lindsay%20Dodgson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffractional-leadership-model-disruptive-success-startups-executives-chris-gannett-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20couple%20started%20buying%20real%20estate%20to%20free%20themselves%20from%2080-hour%20workweeks.%20After%20scaling%20to%20more%20than%20100%20units%2C%20they%20work%20part-time%20and%20travel%20half%20the%20year.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kenji%20leti%20semi-retired%20MD%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c475a3d5881a51c1b6237%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhysician%20couple%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20are%20the%20founders%20of%20Semi-Retired%20MD.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELetizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20started%20buying%20investment%20properties%20together%20in%202015.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20years%2C%20they%20worked%2080-hour%20weeks%20in%20the%20hospital%20and%20wanted%20to%20buy%20back%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20scaled%20to%20over%20100%20units%2C%20hit%20financial%20freedom%2C%20and%20now%20teach%20other%20doctors%20how%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20height%20of%20their%20medical%20careers%2C%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20had%20to%20block%20off%20time%20on%20their%20calendars%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20see%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20would%20schedule%20out%20a%20month%20in%20advance%2C%20days%20that%20we%20could%20spend%20together%20because%20it%20was%20so%20busy%2C%26quot%3B%20Alto%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20this%20was%20without%20us%20having%20kids%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20both%20working%20more%20than%20full-time%20as%20hospitalists%2C%20logging%2080-hour%20weeks.%20When%20they%20took%20a%20step%20back%20and%20considered%20what%20they%20wanted%20their%20future%20to%20look%20like%2C%20the%20grueling%20workweeks%20didn't%20fit%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKenji%20asked%20me%2C%20'What%20do%20you%20really%20want%20for%20your%20life%3F%20Presume%20there%20are%20no%20limits.%20What%20would%20you%20want%20to%20do%3F'%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Alto.%20Her%20answer%20was%20specific%3A%20She%20wanted%20to%20spend%20months%20out%20of%20the%20year%20in%20Italy%2C%20producing%20olive%20oil%20and%20hosting%20friends.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20was%20obviously%20very%20different%20than%20the%20path%20we%20were%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20interesting%20thought%20experiment%20that%20ultimately%20shifted%20their%20mindset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20six%20months%20later%2C%20while%20traveling%20in%20a%20camper%20van%20through%20New%20Zealand%20on%20their%20honeymoon%2C%20they%20passed%20the%20nights%20reading%20what%20Alto%20had%20recently%20downloaded%20to%20her%20Kindle%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-dad-poor-dad-book-review-lessons-money-personal-finance-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERich%20Dad%20Poor%20Dad%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20resonated%20with%20some%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-popular-money-book-rich-dad-poor-dad-robert-kiyosaki-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20author's%20core%20themes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20really%20powerful.%20We%20were%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20my%20gosh%2C%20this%20is%20it%3A%20We're%20employees%2C%20we%20trade%20our%20time%20for%20money%2C%20we're%20never%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20be%20in%20Italy%20for%20three%20months%20at%20a%20time%20because%20we're%20always%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20working%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BThis%20future%20that%20I%20had%20kind%20of%20visualized%20six%20months%20before%20didn't%20work.%20The%20only%20way%20it%20works%20is%20if%20we%20have%20another%20source%20of%20income%2C%20outside%20medicine%2C%20that%20can%20replace%20part%20of%20our%20salaries%20so%20that%20we%20can%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20take%20time%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20decided%20right%20then%20and%20there%20that%20when%20they%20returned%20home%20to%20Seattle%2C%20they'd%20start%20investing%20in%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224abd68f8-344b-43b1-bc46-1eba3e08b2b1%5C%22%3EPutting%20off%20a%20primary%20residence%20in%20order%20to%20buy%20investment%20properties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20additional%20income%20by%20investing%20in%20real%20estate%20made%20sense%20for%20Alto%20and%20Asakura%20for%20a%20few%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20Asakura%20already%20had%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20parents%20were%20investors%20and%2C%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20going%20to%20rental%20properties%2C%20picking%20up%20checks%2C%20seeing%20my%20dad%20talk%20to%20tenants%2C%20things%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20grew%20up%20with%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20pretty%20much%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20had%20money%2C%20I%20started%20investing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20came%20after%20medical%20school%2C%20when%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20management%20consultant%20for%20McKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20for%20a%20few%20years%20before%20completing%20his%20residency.%20Using%20savings%20from%20his%20salaried%20job%2C%20he%20and%20a%20friend%20started%20building%20a%20joint%20portfolio%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20and%2C%20like%20most%20property%20investors%20at%20the%20time%2C%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReal%20estate%20just%20appreciated%20like%20crazy%2C%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20around%202006%2C%202007%2C%20when%20things%20started%20slowing%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asakura%2C%20who%20was%20mainly%20buying%20and%20flipping%20land.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20buy%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20for%20like%20%24100%2C000%20and%2C%20six%20months%20later%2C%20I%20would%20sell%20it%20for%20%24300%2C000.%20It%20was%20that%20crazy.%20It%20was%20just%20like%20the%20Big%20Short.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20recession%20hit%2C%20%26quot%3Bmy%20properties%20didn't%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20I%20got%20stuck%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20mortgages%2C%20insurance%20payments%2C%20and%20property%20taxes.%20I%20was%20pretty%20much%20upside%20down%20on%20my%20properties%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20experience%20didn't%20deter%20him%20from%20re-entering%20the%20real%20estate%20world%20years%20later%20alongside%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20scared.%20If%20anything%2C%20I%20had%20confidence%20just%20because%20we%20had%20a%20plan.%20Mistakes%20are%20an%20expensive%20education%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20best%20education.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22leti%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b298885e81483682bfefb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAsakura%20and%20Alto%20started%20blogging%20in%202018.%20Now%2C%20they%20offer%20courses%20and%20events%20to%20help%20people%20achieve%20%26quot%3BFast%20FIRE.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Asakura's%20experience%2C%20the%20couple%20had%20the%20capital%20to%20invest%20in%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'd%20planned%20to%20buy%20a%20primary%20home%20together%20and%20had%20already%20set%20aside%20cash%20for%20the%20down%20payment.%20But%2C%20after%20returning%20from%20the%20New%20Zealand%20trip%20in%20early%202015%2C%20they%20asked%20their%20agent%20to%20switch%20gears%20and%20help%20them%20find%20a%20rental%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20a%20new%2C%20clear%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20wrote%20down%20our%20portfolio%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20like%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20own%20this%20many%20units%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20make%20this%20much%20cash%20flow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22babcb208-f31e-4398-83ff-c44b387868c7%5C%22%3EBuying%20and%20holding%20cash-flowing%20properties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Alto%20and%20Asakura%20started%20purchasing%20investment%20properties%2C%20their%20strategy%20revolved%20around%20two%20main%20principles%3A%20cash%20flow%20and%20forced%20appreciation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20use%20a%20cash-on-cash%20calculator%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20input%20metrics%20such%20as%20purchase%20price%2C%20expenses%2C%20and%20projected%20rents%20to%20predict%20a%20property's%20performance.%20They're%20less%20interested%20in%20how%20it's%20performing%20under%20the%20current%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20really%20more%20important%20is%20knowing%20how%20it's%20going%20to%20run%20after%20you're%20done%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BWe%20regularly%20buy%20properties%20that%20are%20negative%20or%20have%20really%20low%20cash-on-cash%20returns%20with%20the%20current%20owners.%20What%20we%20see%20is%20the%20potential%20for%20what%20it%20can%20become.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20learned%20from%20Asakura's%20early%20investing%20days%20to%20never%20rely%20on%20market%20appreciation.%20They'd%20rather%20force%20appreciation%20on%20the%20property%20through%20improvements%20and%20upgrades%2C%20which%20isn't%20dissimilar%20to%20a%20flip%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20difference%20is%2C%20a%20flipper%20sells%2C%20whereas%20we're%20holding.%20The%20other%20difference%20is%20that%20a%20flipper%20typically%20buys%20a%20property%20that'll%20never%20cash%20flow%2C%20whereas%20we're%20buying%20properties%20that%20are%20good%20flip%20projects%20but%20also%20cash%20flow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20using%20their%20down%20payment%20savings%2C%20they%20bought%20two%20duplexes%20outside%20Seattle%2C%20filled%20the%20units%20with%20tenants%2C%20and%20started%20generating%20rental%20income.%20They%20continued%20buying%20small%2C%20undervalued%20multi-family%20properties%2C%20used%20tax%20strategies%20to%20shield%20their%20income%20from%20taxes%2C%20and%20rolled%20their%20rental%20income%2C%20savings%2C%20and%20tax%20refunds%20into%20more%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202017%2C%20they%20said%20they%20were%20bringing%20in%20over%20six%20figures%20of%20rental%20cash%20flow.%20The%20next%20year%2C%20they%20started%20their%20blog%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsemiretiredmd.com%2Fabout-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESemi-Retired%20MD%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20evolve%20into%20an%20online%20course%20specifically%20geared%20at%20doctors%20and%20high-income%20earners%20looking%20to%20invest%20in%20real%20estate.%20By%202021%2C%20they%20owned%20over%20150%20personal%20units%20and%20over%20400%20syndicated%20doors.%20BI%20confirmed%20their%20property%20ownership%2C%20which%20includes%20multi-family%20properties%2C%20commercial%20properties%2C%20and%20a%20handful%20of%20syndication%20deals%2C%20by%20reviewing%20deeds%20and%20operating%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Letizia%20alto%20kenji%20asakura%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b29fe85e81483682bff0e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlto%20and%20Asakura%20reside%20in%20Puerto%20Rico%20but%20travel%20about%20six%20months%20a%20year.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20were%20tenants%20themselves%20up%20until%202022%2C%20when%20they%20moved%20to%20Puerto%20Rico%20and%20bought%20their%20first%20primary%20residence%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20never%20chasing%20big%20cash%20flow%20goals%20to%20sit%20on%20the%20beach%20all%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20was%20to%20buy%20ourselves%20time-freedom%20and%20to%20continue%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20world%20and%20have%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20hospital%20up%20until%202020%20and%20now%20spends%20a%20chunk%20of%20her%20days%20running%20Semi-Retired%20MD.%20Asakura%2C%20who%20scaled%20back%20to%20part-time%20in%20the%20hospital%20in%202015%20to%20focus%20on%20real%20estate%2C%20spends%20his%20days%20managing%20their%20portfolio%2C%20and%20they%20both%20have%20more%20time%20to%20dedicate%20to%20each%20other%20and%20their%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20about%20what%20my%20life%20could%20have%20been%20right%20now%3A%20Driving%20to%20work%2C%20spending%2012%20hours%20away%2C%20and%20coming%20home%20late%20at%20night%20when%20the%20kids%20are%20asleep%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asakura.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20how%20our%20lives%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlto%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20our%20kids%20homeschooled.%20We%20travel%20six%20months%20a%20year%20as%20a%20family.%20We%20hang%20out%20with%20our%20kids%20in%20the%20mornings%2C%20we%20see%20them%20for%20lunch%2C%20and%20we%20see%20them%20for%20dinner%20every%20night.%20We%20never%20would%20have%20had%20any%20of%20that%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-profitable-rental-business-retire-early-financial-freedom-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749891301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c494b3d5881a51c1b6282%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-bui